  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries around the world. Some key examples include:\n\n1. In the United States:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN) regulations\n\n2. In the European Union:\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives (AMLD)\n- Comprehensive regulations across EU member states\n\n3. International standards:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\nThese regulations typically require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Monitor and report suspicious transactions\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n- Conduct risk assessments\n\nThe goal is to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income.",
